{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μετασκευ-άζω</b>, <br /> <b>put into another dress</b> (σκευή), <b>change the fashion of, transform</b>, σαυτήν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 499; τὰ ἅρματα εἰς τὸν αὐτὸν τρόπον 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.2.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. νόμον <b>amend</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Dinarchus Orator 1.42 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>put into a fresh shape</b>, τὰς λέξεις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 6. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, <b>exchange one's equipment with another</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Αιβυκή” 8; μ. εἰς τοὺς ὁπλίτας 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 2.60a. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>pack up so as to change one's quarters</b>, τὰ αὑτοῦ παρά τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Xenophon Ephesius Scriptor Eroticus 5.13 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>shift oneself</b>, ἐκ.. εἰς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tox.” 57, compare 3rd c.AD(?): Achilles Tatius Astronomus 3.1. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>clothe oneself differently</b>, οἰκετικαῖς ἐσθήσεσιν μ. <b>disguise oneself</b> in.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Polyaenus Historicus 6.49: \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i>, πόθεν μετεσκεύασθ; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Her.Prooem.” 1. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8303","accentedUnicode":"μετασκευάζω","shortDef":"to fashion differently","mediumDef":"to fashion differently","stepGloss":"to fashion differently","stepTransliteration":"metaskeuazō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}